{"id":"bewray","term":"Bewray","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>To reveal or disclose; an old English word equivalent to “betray” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 27:16\">Prov. 27:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 29:24\">29:24</a>, R.V., “uttereth;” <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 16:3\">Isa. 16:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 26:73\">Matt. 26:73</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Proverbs 27:16","Proverbs 29:24","Isaiah 16:3","Matthew 26:73"]}